We first note that the only “Fixed Assets” entry in the new table is the initial fixed‐assets record from 2023‑12‑31 for an amount of 5,000,000.00. Then, the value of fixed assets is reduced by depreciation transactions. In the data there are two depreciation transactions:
 • On 2024‑01‑01 a Depreciation of 45,756.35
 • On 2024‑02‑01 a Depreciation of 45,752.90
Their total is 45,756.35 + 45,752.90 = 91,509.25

Thus, the net fixed assets at the end of the period is computed as:
 5,000,000.00 – 91,509.25 = 4,908,490.75

So the fixed assets net item in the balance sheet has:
 Initial Value = 5,000,000.00
 End Value     = 4,908,490.75
